==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phalarope
<hw>Phal"a*rope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>falaro`s</grk> having a patch of white + <grk>poy`s</grk>,
<grk>podo`s</grk>, a foot: cf. F. <ets>phalarope</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any species of <gen>Phalaropus</gen> and allied
genera of small wading birds (<ord>Grall⟦ae⟧</ord>), having lobate toes.
They are often seen far from land, swimming in large flocks. Called also
<altname>sea goose</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phalaropidae</ent>⟦br⟧
